Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.46,0:02:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fe134}{\fsp0}{\fad(500,500)}{\pos(190,278)}{\fn方正准圆简体}{\bord0}{\fs20}{\c&H24EFFF&}宇宙大探索\N{\fs17}{\c&HFFFFFF&} 第十集
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.29,0:02:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,也許遲早有那麼一天\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sooner or later,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.00,0:02:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,總有人能作出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}someone would've likely figured out
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.83,0:02:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,他的某些發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}some of his discoveries.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.73,0:02:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,但如果邁克爾·法拉第沒有在這世界上出現過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But if Michael Faraday had never lived,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.27,0:03:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我們現在可能還活在和十七世紀的人們一樣的世界裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}we might still be living as our ancestors did in the 17th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.57,0:03:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,根本不會意識到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Unaware
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.27,0:03:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,我們的身邊有著看不見的力量等待著我們的使喚\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of armies of invisible servants awaiting our commands.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.68,0:03:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,這是關於我們如何掌握了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is the story of how we learned
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.61,0:03:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,電的力量的故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to make electrons do our bidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.42,0:03:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,從某個方面來說 這一切始於一位偉大的天才人物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In a way, it begins with the greatest genius who ever lived--
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.42,0:03:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,艾薩克·牛頓\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Isaac Newton.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.43,0:03:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,這裏是牛頓的故居 伍爾斯索普\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is Woolsthorpe, Newton's ancestral home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.43,0:03:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}位於英國  1642年12月25日 牛頓在此出生
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.27,0:03:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,他在這條小路上總是在那苦苦思索著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He walked these fields, tormented by mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.67,0:03:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,牛頓 正是他發現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Newton, the man who figured out the formula
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.94,0:03:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,行星繞日運動的規律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for the motions of the planets around the Sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.04,0:03:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,他還想知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}wanted to know
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.71,0:03:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽是如何讓行星圍繞著它旋轉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}how does the Sun make the planets act that way
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.35,0:03:41.01,Default,,0,0,0,,而又不用互相接觸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}without touching them?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.01,0:03:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,樹上的蘋果怎麼知道何時該掉落\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How do all the apples know how to fall?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.55,0:03:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,另一位天才同樣從另一個方面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Another genius was puzzled by another aspect
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.55,0:03:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,被這個問題所困擾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the same mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.33,0:03:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,兒子 看哪\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You see, son?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.83,0:04:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,無論我怎樣轉動這個指南針\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No matter how I turn the compass,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.33,0:04:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,針頭總會指向相同的方向\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the needle always points the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.17,0:04:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,除非...\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Except...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.68,0:04:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,怎麼會呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.15,0:04:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,他們根本就沒碰到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They do not touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.35,0:04:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,阿爾伯特 我還沒聽到你說'謝謝'\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I didn't hear a "Thank you," Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.56,0:04:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我依然記得這個故事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I can still remember this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.86,0:04:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,它們給了我深深的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The experience made a deep
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.86,0:04:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,連綿不絕的感動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and lasting impression on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.33,0:04:34.87,Default,,0,0,0,,肯定有某些東西深深地隱藏在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Something deeply hidden
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.90,0:04:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,這一切的背後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}had to be behind things.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.04,0:04:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,在愛因斯坦與牛頓之間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Between the lifetimes of Einstein and Newton,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.21,0:04:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,還出現了另一位天才\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}there lived another genius,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.28,0:04:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,與他們同樣偉大\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one of equal stature.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.54,0:04:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,這位天才解決了困擾牛頓的問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The man who solved the mystery that stumped Newton,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.88,0:04:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,也奠定了愛因斯坦的革命性發現的基礎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}also laid the foundation for Einstein's revolutionary insights.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.62,0:04:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,以及人類今天生存的方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And for the way we live now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.04,0:05:20.34,Default,,0,0,0,,1791年 在倫敦郊區的一個髒兮兮的貧民窟裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In 1791, in a squalid slum in the suburbs of London,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.38,0:05:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,邁克爾·法拉第出生了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Michael Faraday was born.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.45,0:05:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,在學校裏 他顯示不出一丁點的天分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He showed little promise at school.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.09,0:05:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,請告訴我們一個\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Pray tell us a word that begins
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.46,0:05:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,以字母R開頭的單詞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with the letter R.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.47,0:05:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.80,0:05:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,肚子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Wabbit?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.64,0:05:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,應該是「兔子」\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The word is "Rabbit."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.11,0:05:52.61,Default,,0,0,0,,再來一次 這次發音要准啊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Once again, and correctly this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.64,0:05:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,肚子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Wabbit?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.68,0:05:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你在嘲弄我嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Do you mock me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.85,0:05:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,難道我沒有告訴你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Have I not told you how
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.75,0:06:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,怎麼去念R這個字母的發音嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to pronounce the letter R?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.42,0:06:03.65,Default,,0,0,0,,但起碼你能告訴我們你的名字吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Surely you can at least tell us your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.69,0:06:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,邁克爾·法老地 老師\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Michael "Fawaday," ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.36,0:06:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,拿這半個便士\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Take this ha'penny,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.49,0:06:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,買根鞭回來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and buy me a cane,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.63,0:06:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,看我怎麼給你那無禮的弟弟抽一頓\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so that I may give your insolent brother a proper flogging.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.55,0:06:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,史書上再也沒有任何法拉弟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}History does not record that Michael Faraday
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.82,0:06:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,去學校讀書的記載\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ever attended school again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.62,0:06:42.63,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉第承傳了家庭的正統基督教信仰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday took his family's fundamentalist Christian faith
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.66,0:06:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,他的虔誠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.23,0:06:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,是他強大的精神動力源泉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It would always remain a source of strength,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.33,0:06:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,讓他平和而謙遜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}comfort and humility for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.80,0:06:52.37,Default,,0,0,0,,13歲時他被送到一個書籍裝訂廠工作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He was sent to work at a bookbindery at the age of 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.40,0:06:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,白天 他在裝訂書籍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By day, he bound the books,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.51,0:06:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,到了晚上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and by night,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.68,0:06:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,他在讀書\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he read them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.84,0:07:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是他終生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was the beginning of a lifelong fascination
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.84,0:07:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}《電的歷史與現前狀態》
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.25,0:07:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,為電而癡狂的起始\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.93,0:07:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,在書籍裝訂廠裏工作了有些年頭以後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}After years of working in the bookbindery,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.03,0:07:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,21歲的法拉弟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday, now 21,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.33,0:07:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,渴望來到一個更廣闊的世界\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}yearned to escape to a larger world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.77,0:07:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,他的機會來了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}His big break came
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.17,0:07:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,一位顧客給了他一張門票\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when a customer gave him a ticket
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.67,0:07:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,讓他去參加一項挺受歡迎的新休閒活動——\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to a sensational new kind of entertainment--
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.58,0:07:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,公眾科普講座\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}science for the public.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.38,0:07:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,正是在這裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it started right here
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.62,0:07:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,倫敦皇家學院\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at London's Royal Institution.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.92,0:07:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,漢弗萊·戴維不僅僅是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Humphry Davy was not only
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.89,0:07:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,當時首屈一指的科學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one of the leading scientists of his day,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.36,0:07:49.73,Default,,0,0,0,,他也發現了好幾種化學元素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he discovered several chemical elements,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.76,0:07:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,包括鈣和鈉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}including calcium and sodium.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.86,0:07:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,他同時也是一位出色的主持人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He was also a consummate showman.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.20,0:07:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,對於電學原理的初步演示\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And primitive demonstrations of electricity
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.57,0:07:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,深受公眾的歡迎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}never failed as a crowd pleaser.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.74,0:08:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,請把燈光調暗 好嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}May we have the lights lowered, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.88,0:08:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,我現在就要釋放出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I am about to unleash the might
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.05,0:08:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,兩千塊化學電池的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the 2,000 massive chemical batteries
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.65,0:08:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,它們就在我們腳下的地下室裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}stored in the cellar beneath our feet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.79,0:08:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,現在 就是見證神秘的力量的時刻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And now, behold the power of the mysterious force
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.89,0:08:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,它來自於電解液 它將照耀我們的未來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of electrical fluid to illuminate our future.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.95,0:08:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉第忙著做筆記 根本無暇鼓掌\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday was too busy taking notes to applaud.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.32,0:08:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉利創作了一份戴維演講的記錄\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday created a transcript of Davy's lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.69,0:08:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,他把做學徒時學得的技巧都用上了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Using the skills he had learned as an apprentice,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.03,0:09:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,他把這些都放在了這本書裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he bound them into this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.43,0:09:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,也許正是這樣的才能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Perhaps such a gift would bring him to the attention
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.10,0:09:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,讓他得到了這位偉人的注意\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the great man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.55,0:09:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,也許這一切舉動是奔往\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maybe this gesture could be a means of escape
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.02,0:09:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,更廣闊世界的方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to a much larger universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.79,0:09:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,早上好 先生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Good day, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.49,0:09:32.46,Default,,0,0,0,,請幫我把這個包裹交給漢弗萊爵士\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I wish you to deliver this parcel to Sir Humphry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.17,0:09:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,不管怎麼說 這就像一個賭注\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was a long shot, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.01,0:09:44.98,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉利希望能賭中些什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But Faraday hoped something would come of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.01,0:09:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,結果他真的賭中了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And it did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.72,0:09:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,呃 實驗已經準備好了 先生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Uh, the experiment is ready for you now, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.26,0:10:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,安培告訴我說可憐的杜隆\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Ampere tells me that poor Dulong lost an eye
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.19,0:10:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,在做這個實驗時 丟掉了一隻眼睛和三個手指\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and three fingers working with this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.50,0:10:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,我的眼睛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}My eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.87,0:10:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,我的眼睛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}My eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.54,0:10:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,當一場化學實驗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When a chemical experiment blew up in the face
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.41,0:10:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,把知名科學家漢弗萊戴維的臉弄傷之後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the world-renowned scientist Humphry Davy,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.21,0:10:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,他想起了法拉弟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he remembered Michael Faraday,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.38,0:10:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,那個小伙子能一大段一大段地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the lad who had gone through such lengths
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.58,0:10:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,把他的講座記錄並整理下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to copy down and bind the transcript of his lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.89,0:10:40.19,Default,,0,0,0,,年輕人 你真是記憶力超群\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You have a first-rate memory, young man.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.22,0:10:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我正好暫時需要一個秘書\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And I shall have temporary need of a secretary.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.89,0:10:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,先生 我做夢都想著為科學服務\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sir, I dream of a life in service to science.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.76,0:10:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,我建議你還是繼續做好你這份書籍裝訂的工作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I would advise you to stick to the bookbinding.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.53,0:10:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,科學研究殘酷而無情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Science is a harsh mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.07,0:10:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,對了 像你這樣的地位 人又謙虛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Surely, a person of your station and modest means
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.90,0:10:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,應當有自己的生意吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}must have a trade.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.24,0:10:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,做生意的人狠毒而自私\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Trade is vicious and selfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.57,0:11:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,做科學研究的人和藹而品格高尚\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Men of science are amiable and morally superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.24,0:11:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,很好 我就是你在科學界裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I take it I'm the first man of science
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.11,0:11:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,第一位遇到的人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you've ever met.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.75,0:11:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉利最終成為戴維身邊不可或缺的人物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday made himself indispensable to Davy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.99,0:11:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,這份臨時的工作成為他終身的職業\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The temporary job became a permanent one,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.42,0:11:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,英國皇家學會成為他生命的歸宿\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and the Royal Institution became his lifelong home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.23,0:11:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,白天 他在實驗室協助戴維\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By day, he assisted Davy in the lab,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.80,0:11:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,晚上 他就走到樓上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at day's end, he climbed the stairs
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.07,0:11:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,回到他那小小的蝸居\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to the little apartment
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.67,0:11:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,他親愛的妻子莎拉在等待著他\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where his beloved bride Sarah was waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.35,0:11:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,漢弗萊·戴維與化學家威廉·瓦爾森\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Humphry Davy and the chemist William Wollaston
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.95,0:11:47.46,Default,,0,0,0,,在實驗中遇到了和兩個保持距離的物品相關的一個神奇的現象\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}were experimenting with a mysterious phenomenon, one with potentially far-reaching implications.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.69,0:11:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,這個裝置和丹麥科學家奧斯特的試驗相似\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is the identical setup to Orsted's.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.06,0:11:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,現在把線圈閉合 戴維 仔細盯著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now close the circuit, Davy, and watch closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.80,0:12:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,是什麼東西讓針偏離了電線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What could be driving the needle away from the wire?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.67,0:12:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,我知道就好了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Damned if I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.07,0:12:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,不過看上去似乎是通電的線圈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But it's as if the electric current
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.81,0:12:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,讓電線有了類似磁鐵的力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}makes the wire behave like some kind of magnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.34,0:12:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,電流一定具有某種磁力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Electricity must have something to do with magnetism.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.71,0:12:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我們能讓它不斷地運轉就好了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now if we could only get it to turn continuously,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.82,0:12:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,想像一下 如果我們能掌握了這些力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}imagine what might be accomplished
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.92,0:12:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,世界將會有怎樣的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if we could put these forces to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.26,0:12:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,把東西整理好後 法拉弟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}After you tidy up, Faraday,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.76,0:12:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,也許你可以試試你能做點什麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}you might see what you can make of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.03,0:12:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,戴維也許只是開個小玩笑\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Davy may have been having a bit of fun
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.03,0:12:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,嘲弄一下他的年輕助手\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at the expense of his young assistant,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.00,0:12:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,但法拉弟的心中燃起了激情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but Faraday was on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.37,0:12:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,當時 電還只能被用做\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Up to now, electricity had been nothing more
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.37,0:12:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,用來娛樂大眾的新奇玩意\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than an entertaining novelty toy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.58,0:12:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,它被用來創造閃光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It could make a light flash for an instant
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.28,0:12:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,或是讓指南針轉個彎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or turn a compass needle briefly,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.55,0:12:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,但沒有什麼實際的用途\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but it had no practical application.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.52,0:12:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟立即著手設計實驗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday immediately set about designing the experiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.69,0:12:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,把他閒暇的每一刻都用在解決這個問題上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}devoting every moment of his spare time to the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.59,0:12:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,如果法拉弟成功了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If Faraday succeeded,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.79,0:13:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,他就能把無盡的 隱秘的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he would be putting an infinitely large, invisible,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.20,0:13:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,不為人知的電子的力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and as-yet-undiscovered army of electrons
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.70,0:13:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,化為人類所用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at the command of human whim.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.30,0:13:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,這個革命是如果何開始的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How does a revolution begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.87,0:13:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,其實也不用花費太多\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sometimes it doesn't take much.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.08,0:13:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,一塊金屬 一碗水銀\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A piece of metal, a bowl of mercury,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.38,0:13:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,一點黃柏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a bit of cork.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.29,0:13:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,親愛的莎拉 把你的小弟叫下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sarah dear, send your little brother down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.29,0:13:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,我就要開始做個新實驗了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I'm about to try something knew,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.29,0:13:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我想讓他看看\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and I want him to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.73,0:13:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,喬治 由你來開啟這光榮時刻吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why don't you do the honors, Georgie.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.30,0:13:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,它動起來了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There she goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.57,0:13:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,它動起來了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There she goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.41,0:13:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是人類的第一台馬達\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This was the first motor
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.15,0:13:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,它能把電流轉化為無間斷的機械運動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}converting electric current into continuous mechanical motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.69,0:13:58.99,Default,,0,0,0,,看上去弱爆了 是不是\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Looks pretty feeble, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.02,0:14:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,可就是這轉動中的小紡錘\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But that turning spindle
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.29,0:14:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,開啟了一場革命\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is the beginning of a revolution,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.13,0:14:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,一件微小的發明引爆了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one that dwarfs all the shots fired
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.60,0:14:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,一連串的連鎖反應\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and bombs ever detonated
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.66,0:14:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,對人類文明產生了龐大的影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the sheer magnitude of its effect on our civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.77,0:14:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,想像一下 我們現在的商業\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Try to imagine all the businesses,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.14,0:14:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,工業 科技\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}industries, technologies,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.14,0:14:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,我們生活中的種種變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}transformations of the way we live
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.51,0:14:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,都源於這歡樂的一刻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that have their beginnings in that ecstatic moment
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.55,0:14:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,源於法拉弟的實驗室\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in Michael Faraday's laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.68,0:14:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟的新發明的新聞很快傳了出去\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}News of Faraday's invention spread quickly,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.29,0:14:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,一夜之間 戴維的助手成為倫敦的熱門人物\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and suddenly, Davy's assistant was the toast of London.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.22,0:14:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,戴維很不爽\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Davy didn't take it well.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.56,0:14:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,畢竟 他曾發現了好些個元素\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He had, after all, discovered all those elements.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.03,0:14:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,可現在人們都在說 他最大的發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now people were saying that his greatest discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.57,0:14:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,就是發現了法拉弟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was Michael Faraday.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.34,0:14:51.54,Default,,0,0,0,,戴維要確保法拉弟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Davy made sure that Faraday
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.57,0:14:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,很快不再成為新聞\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}wouldn't be making any more headlines anytime soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.05,0:14:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,您找我嗎 先生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You sent for me, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.02,0:15:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,我有個新任務要交給你\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I have a new challenge for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.69,0:15:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我想要你去接下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I want you to take over our efforts
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.75,0:15:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,改進英國光學鏡片質量的任務\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to improve the quality of British optical glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.89,0:15:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,那些該死的巴伐利亞人把我們的市場都佔領了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Those damned Bavarians are running circles around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.99,0:15:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,鏡片\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Glass?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.06,0:15:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,請恕我冒昧 先生\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}With all due respect, sir,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.73,0:15:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,我對鏡片製造一無所知啊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I know nothing at all of glass-making.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.33,0:15:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,那就好好學吧 法拉弟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Then you will learn, Faraday.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.54,0:15:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,反正你學什麼都很快\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We all know what a quick study you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.27,0:15:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,你只需要分析那些鏡片的化學成分\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just analyze the chemical composition of their glass
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.61,0:15:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,再逆向找出它的製造過程\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and work backwards to see how they made it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.61,0:15:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,這不會花很長時間的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It shouldn't take you long.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.05,0:15:40.86,Default,,0,0,0,,可法拉弟苦苦花了4年時間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But Faraday struggled for four years
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.89,0:15:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,依然一無所獲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}without any success.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.57,0:16:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,這次比上一次更糟糕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is even worse than the last batch.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.74,0:16:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,不管他如何努力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No matter how hard he tried,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.78,0:16:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟始終沒能找到約瑟夫•弗勞恩霍夫在數年前的發現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday could not figure out what Joseph Fraunhofer had discovered years before.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.42,0:16:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟失敗在於他沒能掌握生產\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What Faraday failed to grasp was that casting
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.42,0:16:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,完美的光學鏡片的技術與科學原理\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}perfect optical glass for telescopes was a craft as well as a science, and the masters
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.39,0:16:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,這些技術的秘密被巴伐利亞的大師們完好的隱藏起來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in Bavaria kept their secrets under lock and key.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.24,0:16:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉利沒能掌握這些秘密\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday never did learn their secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.77,0:16:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,他把一塊玻璃磚保存了下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He kept a single glass brick
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.24,0:16:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,作為失敗的紀念品\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as a souvenir of this failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.78,0:16:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,幾年後 這塊東西同樣改變了他的生活\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Years later, it would change the course of his life...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.52,0:16:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,還有我們的生活\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.94,0:17:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,戴維的去世最終結束了這項無果的項目\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Davy's death finally brought an end to this fruitless project,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.31,0:17:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,而法拉弟 這個貧民窟的孩子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and Faraday, the boy from the slums,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.28,0:17:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,成為了實驗室的主管\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}succeeded him as Director of the Laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.85,0:17:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟利用他的權力做出了一些史無前例的事情\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday used his new authority to do something unprecedented--
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.52,0:17:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,他從1825年開始舉辦了一系列專門為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a series of annual Christmas lectures on science
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.29,0:17:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,青少年而設的聖誕節年度科普講座\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for the young... beginning in 1825
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.56,0:17:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,並一直延續到了現在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and continuing to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.30,0:17:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}儘管皇家學院的聽課費頗為昂貴 但只要是法拉第講演 講座廳就會擠得水洩不通
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.30,0:17:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}其他人的講座平均只有三分之二的聽眾
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.30,0:17:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}某次的聖誕節講座的主題為《蠟燭的化學史》 被翻譯成各種語言 至今仍在出版
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.30,0:17:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}1846年法拉第在皇家學院代替查理·惠斯通作一次報告 當時惠斯通原定報告他的一些研究工作
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.30,0:17:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}但到了最後一刻他突然驚慌失措爬出會場 法拉第只好作了一個即場演講
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.30,0:17:58.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}法拉第所作的這些演講 在不久之後卻扮演了將科學推廣到社會的重要角色
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.66,0:18:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,在某個首次舉辦的聖誕節講座上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}At one of the first Christmas lectures,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.23,0:18:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉利讓他的聽眾們著迷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday enchanted his audience
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.40,0:18:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,他展示了他所掌握的新能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with displays of the new powers that were at his disposal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.33,0:18:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,假設我要點著這堆火藥\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Suppose I want to fire a portion of gunpowder.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.04,0:18:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我很輕鬆的就可以 通過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I can readily do it with the power
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.84,0:18:14.31,Default,,0,0,0,,電的力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.38,0:18:22.08,Default,,0,0,0,,如果我通過這根電纜讓電流經過我的身體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If I receive electricity through this conducting wire,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.11,0:18:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,那我就能把電導到我接觸的作任何物體上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I can then give it to anything I touch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.45,0:18:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,不過我得先站到這張有玻璃絕緣腿的凳子上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But I must stand on these insulating glass leg
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.69,0:18:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,不然電流就會跑到地板上\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to prevent the electricity from going away into the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.09,0:18:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,現在 我通電了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now I am electrified!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.56,0:18:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,哇\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.87,0:18:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我就靠我這根手指\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Do you think I could light this gas jet
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.64,0:18:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,能點著這盞汽燈麼\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}just by touching it with my finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.91,0:18:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不要啊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No, don't do it! No!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.08,0:18:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,不 不要\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}No! Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.55,0:18:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,小朋友在家裏不要學 叔叔有練過的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now, mind you, don't try this at home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.25,0:19:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,現在 孩子們 用你們的眼睛看吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And now, my children, you have seen for yourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.32,0:19:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是看不見的電的力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}how this invisible force of electricity
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.89,0:19:10.29,Default,,0,0,0,,它能為我們做更多的事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}can be made to serve new purposes
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.33,0:19:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,但以我們目前的力量還不能完全做到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}utterly unattainable by the powers we have now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.84,0:19:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,馬達的發明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The invention of a motor that could work continuously,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.84,0:19:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}港譯 摩達
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.91,0:19:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,能讓人類從勞苦的工作中釋放出來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}eliminating countless human hours of drudgery,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.11,0:19:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,能讓人類更加富裕\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would be more than enough to make you a fortune
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.08,0:19:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,也能讓人永載史冊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and land you in the history books.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.09,0:19:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,但法拉弟沒有看到這些\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But that's not how Michael Faraday saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.69,0:19:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,他從來沒有申請專利的念頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He had absolutely no interest in patenting his ideas
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.86,0:19:41.83,Default,,0,0,0,,也沒想過從中獲私利\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or personally profiting from them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.86,0:19:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,至於史書\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And as for the history books,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.86,0:19:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,他僅僅寫下第一行字\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he had only written the first sentence
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.10,0:19:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,後面的許多篇章都來不及了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of an entry that would be many pages long.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.87,0:19:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,安德森先生 請把燈光調暗吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Mr. Anderson, may I ask you to dim the lights, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.01,0:19:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,先生們 只需動一動這塊磁鐵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Gentlemen, I am about to induce a current of electricity
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.14,0:19:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,就可以製造出電流\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}merely by moving a magnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.21,0:20:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,請好好觀察吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Please observe what happens
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.78,0:20:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,在我這樣做的時候 請好好看著線圈的間隙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the gap between the wires when I do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.46,0:20:13.83,Default,,0,0,0,,你們看到了磁鐵在運行時電流是如何流動的嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Do you see how the current only flows when the magnet is moving?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.23,0:20:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是將\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is the conversion
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.80,0:20:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,動能轉為化為電能\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of motion into electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.31,0:20:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是人類第一台發電機\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This was the first generator.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.41,0:20:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,從此 電能被人類掌控\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}From here, electricity would become available on demand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.75,0:20:39.32,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟在不斷地改變著世界以及人類的生活\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday was continuing to change the world and the way people lived,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.35,0:20:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,然而 天嫉英才\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and then, suddenly,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.42,0:20:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,病魔侵襲了他那舉世無雙的大腦\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an illness attacked his incomparable mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.26,0:20:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,親愛的捨恩拜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}My dear Schoenbein,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.33,0:20:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我很高興看到你的觀點 我認為…\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I would be very grateful to have your opinion regarding...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.34,0:21:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我認為…\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Regarding...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.51,0:21:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,親愛的捨恩拜…我認為…\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Dear Schoenbein... Regarding...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.09,0:21:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,老公 怎麼了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}My dear husband, whatever is the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.63,0:21:23.33,Default,,0,0,0,,我想寫封信給捨恩拜\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I began a letter to Schoenbein
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.36,0:21:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,可就是記不得我想要寫什麼了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and could not remember what I meant to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.30,0:21:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,別擔心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is no cause for alarm.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.53,0:21:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,你工作太累了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You work too hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.40,0:21:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,-已經精疲力盡了 -不是的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}- You're exhausted. - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.57,0:21:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,莎拉 這次不一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sarah, this is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.87,0:21:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,真的很不一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Horribly different.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.87,0:21:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,我的大腦出現這樣的問題很多天了 這是第三次了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's the third time my memory has failed me in as many days.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.41,0:21:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,只怕我要失去我的記憶力了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}I fear I'm losing my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.55,0:21:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我該如何是好\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And what would I be without that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.48,0:21:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,老公 別擔心 會好的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Why, my darling husband, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.89,0:21:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟49歲時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When Faraday was 49,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.89,0:21:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,他便開始面臨失憶與抑鬱癥的困擾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he began to battle severe memory loss and depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.90,0:21:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,這使得他的工作陷入了停頓\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}His work came to a standstill.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.43,0:22:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,雖然他從此沒有完全康復過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And although he never fully recovered,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.80,0:22:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,但他更大的發現還在後頭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}his greatest achievements still lay ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.92,0:22:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟完全地沉浸在電力與磁力的實驗中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday had immersed himself so deeply in electrical and magnetic experiments
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.80,0:22:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,他觀察到磁鐵的周圍\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that he came to visualize the space around a magnet
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.54,0:22:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,有看不見的力場線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as filled with invisible lines of force.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.24,0:22:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,磁鐵不僅僅是一塊磁化的小鐵塊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A magnet was not simply the magnetized bar of iron
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.68,0:22:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,不僅僅是肉眼所見的一切\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that you could see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.08,0:22:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,還有某些我們看不見的東西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was also the unseen something
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.91,0:22:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,圍繞著磁鐵四周的空間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the space around the bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.48,0:22:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,他稱之為場\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And that something he called a field.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.98,0:22:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是磁場\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}A magnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.39,0:22:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟認為在自然界這個統一的整體中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday believed in the unity of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.09,0:22:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,無處不在展示著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Having demonstrated the connections
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.49,0:22:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,電場與磁場的關連\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}between electricity and magnetism, he wondered,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.26,0:23:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,這兩者會不會與第三種能量——光 相關連\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}were these two forces also connected to a third-- light?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.00,0:23:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,如果他能展示出\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If he could only show a connection
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.27,0:23:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,這三種不可見現象之間的關連\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}among these three invisible phenomena,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.07,0:23:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,那麼自然界最隱秘的奧秘之一\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one of nature's most intimate secrets
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.61,0:23:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,就會被人類揭開\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}would at last be revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.54,0:23:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,最終 他是怎麼做的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So, what did he do?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.58,0:23:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,他設計了一項試驗\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He designed an experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.42,0:23:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟知道光能像波一樣傳播\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday knew that light can travel as a wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.45,0:23:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,光波在各個方向隨機振動\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Waves of light vibrate randomly in all directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.52,0:23:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,但有個方法可以固定某個特定的光波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But there's a way to isolate a single wave of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.13,0:23:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,這個方法就是偏振\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It's called polarization.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.13,0:23:28.83,Default,,0,0,0,,當光從反射面反彈回來時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When light bounces off a reflective surface,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.86,0:23:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,比如一面鏡子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}like a mirror,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.30,0:23:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,就會出現偏振\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}it becomes polarized.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.87,0:23:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟想知道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday wanted to see
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.74,0:23:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,一條單束的光線是否能被\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if that single ray of light could be manipulated
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.87,0:23:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,不可見的磁場所控制\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}by the invisible magnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.91,0:23:42.41,Default,,0,0,0,,這塊目鏡含有水晶\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The eyepiece contained a crystal
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.44,0:23:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,它就如同一道柵欄擋住了光線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that acted as a kind of picket fence for light.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.41,0:23:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,如果光線想要穿過它\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Light could only pass through it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.42,0:23:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,就必須受磁場的影響而偏移\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if it was somehow moved by the magnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.88,0:23:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,他在鏡子前面放了一盞燈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He placed a lantern before a mirror,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.09,0:23:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,如果他能通過目鏡看到燈光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}one that he would only see through the eyepiece
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.29,0:23:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,那說明反射光穿過了柵欄\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if its reflection could pass through the picket fence.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.93,0:24:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,如果你覺得很難理解 這很正常\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}If this is hard to understand, don't feel bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.16,0:24:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,在這之後的100年裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Scientists could not explain this phenomenon
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.10,0:24:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,科學家們也不能解釋這種現象\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for another 100 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.80,0:24:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉利知道磁場\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday knew that magnetism had no effect
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.84,0:24:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,對空氣中移動的光線沒有任何影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}on light that was moving through air.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.81,0:24:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,可要是光線在其他物體中移動呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But what about when it was moving through other materials?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.08,0:24:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,他又能使用那種物體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So what kind of material could he use
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.44,0:24:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,來幫助磁場移動光線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to help the magnet move the light?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.08,0:24:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,他測試了好幾百種\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He tried hundreds of different
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.18,0:24:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,透明的化學物質與物品\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}transparent chemicals and objects...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.95,0:24:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,可還是什麼也看不到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but saw nothing through the eyepiece.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.96,0:24:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,光線沒有因磁場發生扭曲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The light was not twisted by the magnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.59,0:24:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,他測試了方解石晶體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He tried crystals of calcite,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.46,0:24:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,碳酸鈉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}sodium carbonate,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.50,0:24:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,硫酸鈣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}calcium sulfate,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.37,0:24:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,可還是什麼都看不見\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and still, he saw nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.00,0:24:41.74,Default,,0,0,0,,他測試了好幾種酸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He tried acids.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.77,0:24:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,硫酸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Sulfuric acid,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.84,0:24:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,鹽酸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}muriatic acid,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.67,0:24:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,碳酸\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}carbonic acid.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.71,0:24:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,還有氣體…\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He tried gasses...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.18,0:24:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,氧氣 氮氣 氫氣…\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}oxygen, nitrogen, hydrogen...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.11,0:24:52.75,Default,,0,0,0,,均以失敗告終\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with no success.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.78,0:24:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,受這些物質所感應的磁場\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The magnetic field induced
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.38,0:24:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,都不能使光線產生扭曲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in these substances could not twist the light
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.72,0:24:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,讓他看到油燈的燈光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from his lamp back into view.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.02,0:25:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,見鬼了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Damn!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.56,0:25:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,無奈之下 他決定要試一試\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}In desperation, he decided to try...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.40,0:25:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,那塊玻璃磚\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the glass brick,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.40,0:25:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,來自於他那段被戴維所束縛時間的那個紀念品\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the souvenir of his years of bondage to Davy.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.75,0:25:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,見效了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It did the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.22,0:25:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,磁場的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The force of the magnet
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.02,0:25:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,使光線產生了扭曲\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}twisted the light
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.76,0:25:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,從而穿越了水晶\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so that it could pass through the crystal.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.36,0:25:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,那麼 這當中有什麼重大意義呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So, what's the big deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.73,0:25:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉第揭示了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday had demonstrated the existence
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.00,0:25:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我們身邊存在的物理現實\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the physical reality that surrounds us,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.60,0:25:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,那是前人所不知道的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but which no one had ever been able to detect.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.41,0:25:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,這是一個激動人心的時刻\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was as dramatic a breakthrough
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.44,0:25:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,猶如人類第一次\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as seeing the cosmos for the very first time
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.21,0:25:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,通過望遠鏡看到宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}through a telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.61,0:26:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,通過展示電磁力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By showing that an electromagnetic force
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.28,0:26:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,可以操縱光線\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}could manipulate light,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.12,0:26:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟發現了自然界深層存在的一種力的聯結\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday had discovered a deeper unity of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.55,0:26:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,他為愛因斯坦打開了一道大門\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He had opened a door for Einstein
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.12,0:26:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,也為後世的物理學家開創了新的天地\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and all the physicists who came after him
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.73,0:26:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,讓人類可以窺見\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to glimpse the interplay
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.53,0:26:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙深處中最基本的隱秘力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of hidden, primal forces in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.76,0:26:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,即使是在達到他的天才的頂峰之時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even as he approached the summit of his genius,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.87,0:26:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,他還在為抑鬱癥所困擾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he was plagued by depression
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.04,0:26:23.70,Default,,0,0,0,,一直在懷疑自己的能力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and doubts about his ability
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.74,0:26:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,能不能記住最簡單的問題\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to retain even the simplest thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.07,0:26:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,朋友們 我發現我很難回答\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}My dear friend, I find a difficulty in answering
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.11,0:26:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,或是正確地瞭解科學論文的內容\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or even acknowledging properly a scientific letter,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.08,0:26:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,因為我記不住東西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for I cannot now hold it at once in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.25,0:26:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我有一部分記憶力不行了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The memory of the parts fail me.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.26,0:26:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,還有 很遺憾你會看到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}P.S. You will be sorry to see
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.73,0:26:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,後面這段提示的話\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the tone of this short note,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.63,0:26:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,我親愛的老公已經和平時不一樣了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but my dearest husband is not quite so well as usual,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.50,0:26:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,希望他能變好吧\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but I hope he will improve.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.07,0:26:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,你真誠的莎拉·法拉弟\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Yours very truly, S. Faraday.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.17,0:27:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,年輕時 法拉弟自貧困中崛起\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}As a young man, Faraday had risen from poverty,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.61,0:27:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,在一個對出身階級非常注重的社會中成長\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in one of the most class-conscious societies
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.08,0:27:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,這是當時世界上階級劃分最嚴格的社會\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the world has ever known,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.45,0:27:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,並成為當時最負盛名的科學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to become the most celebrated scientist of his time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.35,0:27:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,40歲的時候 他發明了電動馬達\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By age 40, he had invented the electric motor,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.95,0:27:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,變壓器 發電機\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the transformer, the generator,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.66,0:27:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,這些設備改變了家庭\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}machines that would change everything about the home,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.69,0:27:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,農場 工廠裏的一切\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the farm, the factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.13,0:27:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,現在 在60歲的時候 在這位偉大的物理學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Now, at 60, decades after the fertile periods
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.80,0:27:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,作出一系列巨大發現後的幾十年\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the greatest physicists,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.04,0:27:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他被失憶和抑鬱所困擾\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}plagued by memory loss and melancholy,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.84,0:27:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,但他無畏地繼續深入探索\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he fearlessly probed deeper
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.94,0:27:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,那看不見的神秘力量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into the mysterious invisible forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.75,0:27:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,在世人認為法拉弟已經過時的時候\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The world thought that Michael Faraday was a has-been.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.82,0:28:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,他無視憂鬱癥\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Despite his depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.76,0:28:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,一如既往地充滿好奇心\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he remained as passionately curious as ever.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.10,0:28:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,在發現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Having discovered the unity
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.66,0:28:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,電 磁 光三者的有機聯繫之後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of electricity, magnetism and light,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.17,0:28:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟想要知道自然界中這三者的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday needed to know
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.00,0:28:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,是如何合而為一 共同發揮作用的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}how this trinity of natural forces work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.14,0:28:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,歌詞：這就是小姐走過的路\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}♪ this is the way the ladies walk... ♪
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.48,0:28:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,其實也沒有什麼新鮮的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This was nothing new.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.08,0:28:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,孩子們早已\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Children had been playing with magnets
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.68,0:28:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,把磁鐵與鐵屑混在一起玩了好幾個世紀了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and iron filings for centuries.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.65,0:28:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,人們一直都認為那些好玩的圖案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Everyone had always assumed that this lovely pattern
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.25,0:28:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,是鐵的作用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}was just something that iron did.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.67,0:28:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟已經知道通電後的電線具有磁性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday knew that electric current turns a wire into a magnet,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.96,0:28:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 他希望在電線外的鐵屑中\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}so he expected to find related patterns
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.33,0:28:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,也能發現類似的圖案\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in iron filings around a wire carrying electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.68,0:28:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,當其他人看到的只是好玩的圖案時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But where others saw merely lovely shapes,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.97,0:28:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟則看得更為深遠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday saw something profound.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.67,0:28:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,這些圖案不僅是鐵屑的變化那麼簡單\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The patterns were not simply a quirk of iron filings;
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.15,0:28:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,它們在磁鐵的四周存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}they existed in the space around a magnet
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.15,0:28:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,也在電流四周出現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}or an electric current,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.72,0:29:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,不管有沒有鐵屑出現\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}even in the absence of iron filings.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.29,0:29:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,這些圖案就是軌跡 足跡\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The patterns were the traces, the footprints
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.02,0:29:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,來自那看不見的能量\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of invisible fields of force,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.16,0:29:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,在任何一個磁性物體外都同樣存在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that reached out into the space around anything magnetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.30,0:29:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,指南針的原理\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The compass needle that people wondered at
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.27,0:29:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,曾讓人類困擾了千年之久\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for a thousand years was not reacting
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.01,0:29:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,其實並不是因為遙遠的北極那裏有塊磁鐵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to some far away magnetic North Pole.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.64,0:29:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,而是因為連續不斷的磁力場\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was detecting a continuous force field
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.18,0:29:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,無處不在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that stretched all the way there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.12,0:29:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,地球本身就是一塊巨大的磁鐵\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Earth itself is a giant magnet.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.59,0:29:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,與其他磁鐵類似\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And like any other magnet,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.12,0:29:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,它的磁力線延展到\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}its lines of force extend far out
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.62,0:29:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,地球四周的空間\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into the space surrounding it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.13,0:29:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,它圍繞著我們 無處不在\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They're everywhere, all around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.26,0:29:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,它們一直存在著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They've always been.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.03,0:29:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,但從沒有人注意過它們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But nobody had ever noticed them before.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.80,0:29:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,或者說 沒有人類注意過\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nobody human, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.97,0:29:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,鳥類是恐龍的後裔\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Birds are the last living descendants of the dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.34,0:30:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,鴿子與其他的鳥類同樣具有出色的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Pigeons and other birds are remarkably good
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.51,0:30:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,識別路途的能力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}at finding their way around.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.45,0:30:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,它們能遷徙千里而不迷路\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They can migrate thousands of miles without getting lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.82,0:30:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,它們是怎麼做到的 部分是由於可識別的地標\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}How? Partly by recognizing familiar landmarks--
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.89,0:30:14.26,Default,,0,0,0,,例如河流 山脈 星辰\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}rivers, mountains, stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.29,0:30:15.96,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至是某種氣味\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Even certain smells can serve
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.99,0:30:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,都能成為遷徙鳥類的路標\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as signposts for migrating birds.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.16,0:30:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,鳥類的體內還有天然的羅盤\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}But birds also have an inner compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.73,0:30:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,它們能感應到地球的磁場\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They can actually sense the Earth's magnetic field.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.97,0:30:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,它們的大腦處理磁場數據的方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Their brains process magnetic data in much the same way
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.74,0:30:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,和人類處理視覺的方式很相似\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}ours process visual data.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.34,0:30:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,依靠感應磁場方位\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By sensing the direction of the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.71,0:30:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,鳥類能分辨南北\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}birds can tell north from south.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.81,0:30:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是為何北美洲的鳥類能夠\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}That's one way North American birds know which way to go
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.85,0:30:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,在冬天找到去往南方的路\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}when they head south for the winter.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.58,0:30:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,地球磁場在兩極\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The field is stronger near the poles
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.92,0:30:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,比赤道的要強\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}than it is at the equator,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.76,0:30:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,鳥類據此可以推斷出它們所在的緯度\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a fact that birds use to figure out their latitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.36,0:30:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,地球磁場中還存在著許多微小的不規則的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}There are also small irregularities in the field,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.03,0:30:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,在這些不規則的地方\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}locations where the field
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.50,0:30:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,磁場會有強弱不同的變化\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}is a little weaker or stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.93,0:30:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,就像是獨特的山脈和河流一樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Just like a distinctive mountain or river,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.37,0:31:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,這些不一樣的磁場也能作為地標\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}these magnetic anomalies can serve as landmarks.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.18,0:31:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,幾千年來人們一直在使用信鴿\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For thousands of years, humans have used carrier pigeons
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.29,0:31:17.15,Default,,0,0,0,,在長距離傳遞信件\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to send messages to distant locations.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.19,0:31:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,這是一種非常重要的信息傳遞方式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It was a crucial method of communication
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.36,0:31:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,到了二戰時也是如此\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as recently as World War II.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.23,0:31:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,因此 人類實際上也已經\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When you think about it, we've been using
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.93,0:31:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,利用磁場來進行通訊有很長一段時間了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}magnetic fields to communicate for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.96,0:31:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,只是我們不知道而已\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}We just didn't know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.97,0:31:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,那地球為什麼會有磁場呢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}So why does our planet have a magnetic field at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.64,0:31:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,它是如何產生的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}What causes it?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.41,0:31:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,答案就在地球的深處\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The answer lies deep inside the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.65,0:31:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,在地球自轉的同時 液態的鐵在繞著實心的地核旋轉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Liquid iron, circulating around the solid part of the core as Earth rotates,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.32,0:31:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,就好像是電流繞著線圈運行\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}acts like a wire carrying an electric current.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.09,0:31:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,就像法拉弟展示的那樣\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And as Faraday showed us,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.93,0:31:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,電流產生了磁場\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}electric currents produce magnetic fields.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.50,0:31:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,這對人類而言是件好事\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And that's a good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.10,0:32:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,磁場讓我們避免宇宙射線的猛烈攻擊\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our magnetic field protects us from the onslaught
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.50,0:32:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,否則生物圈就會遭到巨大傷害\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of cosmic rays, which would be very damaging to our biosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.60,0:32:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙射線可以穿透\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Cosmic rays can rip through DNA.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.94,0:32:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有磁場的保護\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Without our magnetic field, the rate of mutation
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.34,0:32:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,生物有機體的變異率會變高\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in living organisms would be much higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.51,0:32:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,幸好 大部分的射線粒子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Fortunately, most of this cosmic shrapnel gets trapped
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.68,0:32:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,會被范艾倫幅射帶所困住 它看上去就像個甜甜圈\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the Van Allen belts, donut-shaped zones
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.45,0:32:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,帶電的粒子會被地球磁場的防護層所攔下\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of charged particles corralled by our magnetic shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.00,0:32:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,明白了地球自身就是一個大磁棒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Knowing that the Earth itself is like a giant bar magnet
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.43,0:32:39.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我們就可以解釋天空中最美麗景觀之一的形成\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}explains one of the most beautiful sights in the sky,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.50,0:32:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是極光\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the aurora.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.71,0:32:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,來自太陽的帶電粒子 也就是太陽風\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Charged particles from the Sun, the solar wind,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.31,0:32:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,在不斷地轟擊地球\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}are constantly bombarding the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.15,0:32:52.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我們可以反把太陽風想像為某種電流\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}You can think of the solar wind as a kind of electric current.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.68,0:32:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,地球的磁場\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Our planet's magnetic field
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.79,0:32:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,在把這股電流導向南極與北極 並在這之間形成了電流渠道\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}channels that current towards the North and South Poles.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.46,0:32:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,當它與大氣碰撞時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When it hits our atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.29,0:33:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,空氣中氧分子與氮分子\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the oxygen and nitrogen molecules
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.13,0:33:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,就會像巨大的螢光燈一樣發出光芒\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the air glow like giant fluorescent lightbulbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.08,0:33:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,當法拉第在繼續進行著\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When Faraday pursued
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.69,0:33:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,最後也是最具有重大意義的發現時\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}his last and most profound discovery,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.09,0:33:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,貧窮的童年對他的影響\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}the poverty of his childhood stymied him
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.09,0:33:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,比以往任何時刻都要明顯的顯現出來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as it never had before.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.86,0:33:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,他需要幫助\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He needed help
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.59,0:33:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,結果 是另一個與他出身不同的人幫助了他\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and found it in one who had come from another world.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.74,0:33:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉利解開了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Michael Faraday had solved the mystery
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.91,0:33:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,困惑牛頓已久的謎團\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}that baffled Isaac Newton.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.50,0:34:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是太陽如何令行星圍繞著它運轉\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This was how the Sun told the planets how to move
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.27,0:34:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,又不用接觸到它們\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}without touching them.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.57,0:34:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,太陽實際上還是接觸得到行星的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}The Sun does touch the planets
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.77,0:34:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,通過它的引力場的作用\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}with its gravitational field,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.91,0:34:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,而地球的引力場\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and Earth's gravitational field
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.24,0:34:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,則告訴蘋果何時該掉下來\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}tells the apples how to fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.55,0:34:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,所有這一切只是一個夢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}All this is a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.16,0:34:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,不幸的是 這就是當時的流行觀點\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Unfortunately, that was the prevailing view
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.00,0:34:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,與他同時代的科學家們認為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}among his fellow scientists.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.60,0:34:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟在做夢\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday was dreaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.87,0:34:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,他們尊重他的創造能力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They admired his inventiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.50,0:34:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,與他天才的實驗能力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and his genius for experimentation,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.57,0:34:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,但他們認為他那看不見的「力線」\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but they regarded his invisible "lines of force"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.41,0:35:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,與他關於光和引力的觀點是臆造的\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and his ideas about light and gravity as hand-waving,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.88,0:35:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有任何可靠的實證可以支持\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}meaning there was nothing solid to back it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.21,0:35:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,有人公開譴責他的理論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Some openly ridiculed his theories.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.42,0:35:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,他們需要看到他的理論\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}They needed to see his ideas expressed
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.75,0:35:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,能被現代物理學的語言所解釋\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}in the language of modern physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.22,0:35:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,也就是精確的數學方程式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}precise equations.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.92,0:35:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,而這個方面\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This was the one area
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.39,0:35:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,由於法拉弟的童年很貧窮\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}where Faraday's childhood poverty
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.06,0:35:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,沒有得到過正式的教育\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and lack of formal education
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.43,0:35:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,因此成為了他的缺陷\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}actually held him back.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.03,0:35:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,他不懂得數學運算\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He couldn't do the math.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.73,0:35:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟最終遇到了他無法跨越的障礙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday had finally hit a wall that he could not overcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.30,0:35:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,而這時 另一位\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}And then, the greatest theoretical physicist
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.91,0:35:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,被公認為19世紀最偉大的理論物理學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of the 19th century came along.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.74,0:35:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯·克拉克·麥克斯韋 出生在一個富裕的家庭裏\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}James Clerk Maxwell was born into a world of wealth
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.91,0:35:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,家裏很有權力\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and privilege,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.55,0:35:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,他的父母中年得子 他是家裏唯一的孩子 深得寵愛\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}an only child of doting middle-aged parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.56,0:35:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,當他才20出頭時 就已經\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}By his early 20s, he had made a name for himself
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.76,0:35:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,成為一個知名的數學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as a mathematician.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.50,0:35:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,當時其他的科學家認為法拉第\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}While other scientists had come to think of Faraday
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.90,0:36:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,已經過時了 是歷史遺老\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}as old-fashioned; {\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a great figure of the past
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.33,0:36:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,根本就不是屬於未來的物理學者\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}but no part of the future of physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.17,0:36:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,麥克斯韋有不同的想法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}James Clerk Maxwell knew better.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.64,0:36:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,他認真的閱讀了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He began by reading everything
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.64,0:36:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,法拉弟所寫的關於電學的一切著作\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Faraday had written on electricity.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.25,0:36:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,他堅信法拉第所提到的力場\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}He became convinced that Faraday's fields of force
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.25,0:36:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,是真實存在的 並且開始動手\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}were real, and he set out to give them
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.75,0:36:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,用精確的數學方程式來證明這一切\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}a precise mathematical formulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.39,0:36:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}論法拉第力線
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.80,0:37:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,物理學中的數學方程式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}An equation in physics is just a shorthand description
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.64,0:37:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,是對某種在特定空間和時間中出現的物理現象的描述\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}of something that can be represented in space and time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.14,0:37:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,例如 描述鐘擺弧線的方程式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}For instance, the equation that describes the arc of a pendulum
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.58,0:37:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,描述了它無論如何也不可能擺動得比起始點高\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}shows that it can never swing higher than its initial height.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.73,0:37:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,當麥克斯韋把法拉利的實驗現象轉化為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}When Maxwell translated Faraday's experimental
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.90,0:37:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,電磁學的方程式後\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}observation on electromagnetic fields into equations,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.00,0:37:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,他又發現了其中的不對稱性\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}he discovered an asymmetry.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.17,0:37:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,看見底部那一條沒有\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}See that bottom one?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.18,0:37:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,它急切地需要某些東西\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It cries out for something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.75,0:37:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,作為一位偉大的數學家\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Great mathematician that he was,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.75,0:37:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,麥克斯韋在其後加了一個單項以平衡方程式\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Maxwell added a single term to balance it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.22,0:38:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,方程式的這一調整改變了法拉弟的靜態磁場\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This tweaking of the equation changed Faraday's static field
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.89,0:38:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,使它變成了能以光速向外傳播的波\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into waves that spread outward at the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.76,0:38:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,沒過多久 人類就發現了\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}It wasn't long before we found a way to turn those waves...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.76,0:38:13.23,Default,,0,0,0,,把這些波轉為\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into couriers
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.27,0:38:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,傳遞信息工具的方法\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}for our messages.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.14,0:38:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你能看到我嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Can you see me?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.07,0:38:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,你能聽到我嗎\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Can you hear me?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.47,0:38:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,這就是根源\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This is how.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.80,0:38:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,這項技術改變了人類的文明\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}This technology has transformed human civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.37,0:38:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,世界從一個個東拼西湊起來的城市\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}from a patchwork of cities,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.50,0:38:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,還有小鎮和鄉村\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}towns and villages
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.51,0:38:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,變成了互通信息的社會組織體\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}into an intercommunicating organism...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.79,0:38:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,信息以光速進行傳播\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}linking us at light speed...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.86,0:39:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,連接著地球上的每一個人\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}to each other...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.37,0:39:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至是宇宙\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}and to the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.71,0:39:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,世上的一切都很美好\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}Nothing is too wonderful to be true,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.98,0:39:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,只要它能符合自然規律\N{\fn微软雅黑\fs14}if it be consistent with the laws of nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.00,0:39:59.79,Default,,0,0,0,,中文翻譯 幸福的微笑 timhal
